{ ABBERLEY HILLS}are part of a range which stretches southwards to the{ {Malverns}through {Woodbury}and { {Ankerdine. }
There were several small quarries whose stone was used in local building, but in{1951}permission was granted to quarry the south-east side of Abberley Hill facing Astley. Local people became progressively more alarmed as huge bites were taken out of the hill with old woodlands being destroyed in the process.
Such was the concern that in {JULY {1977}the {ABBERLEY HILLS PRESERVATION {SOCIETY}was formed. Its objects are to promote interest in the Abberley Hills, in their history and natural history and to preserve the amenities of the area for the public benefit.
